[gd_resource type="TileSet" load_steps=7 format=3 uid="uid://b0embergrave_s1yard_tileset"]

; S1 cloister-YARD TileSet — ticket 86ca5erzk (T4) + the v2 GROUND-COMPOSITION RE-DO
; (86ca5hwmx, Uma s1-ground-composition-v2.md). After the ASHLAR SLAB path was soak-
; rejected a THIRD time, the path + ground were re-specced: the path is FINE-COBBLE
; PAVERS (a finer+warmer variant of the LOVED cobble gen), and the ground is now a
; VARIED composition (worn DIRT majority + GRASS reclamation patches + COBBLE patches
; + the fine-cobble lane), NOT a wall-to-wall cobble carpet. Five 32px atlas sources:
;
;   Source 0 = floor_cobble.png → the LOVED ground cobble (LOCKED): warm-grey domed
;                set-stones (gen_s1_cobble_floor.py --profile cobble), ~18px largest
;                at game zoom ≈ 1/3 player. Now used for the surviving-paving PATCHES
;                (~10-20% of the ground), NOT a carpet. 768x128 = SIX 4x4 variant-
;                blocks (variant v = cols [v*4 .. v*4+3]); painter scatters per block.
;   Source 1 = wall_cloister_fine.png → finer-brick perimeter (T2). 128x128 = 4x4,
;                period 4.
;   Source 2 = floor_path.png → the v2 FINE-COBBLE LANE (gen_s1_cobble_floor.py
;                --profile path). REPLACES the dead floor_slab.png ashlar (third
;                rejection) + the twice-rejected floor_sandstone.png. The SAME loved
;                Voronoi cobble tech, tuned FINER (largest stone ~10-14px, finer than
;                the ground cobble) + WARMER+LIGHTER (S1_PATH_COBBLE_DOCTRINE) for the
;                "walk here" path-vs-ground contrast (spec §2). ZERO baked green
;                (joints are dirt-shadow #3D372F only — PL-PATH-04). 768x128 = SIX 4x4
;                variant-blocks like cobble; the painter scatters variants down the
;                lane to break the repeating stamp (spec §2.4).
;   Source 3 = floor_dirt.png → the new MAJORITY worn-DIRT field (~55-65%;
;                gen_s1_cobble_floor.py --profile dirt). Stone-free toroidal-noise
;                worn-earth (#6B5A41/#54452F + worn-lighter/damp-darker), seamless,
;                ZERO green (PL-PATH-04). The default ground (Graveyard-Keeper ref).
;                768x128 = SIX 4x4 variant-blocks.
;   Source 4 = floor_grass.png → the GRASS reclamation tile (~20-30%, edges/corners;
;                gen_s1_cobble_floor.py --profile grass). A clean noise-driven green
;                GROUND material (the deliberate-planting foundation), painted as
;                PATCHES with feathered borders — NOT the rejected spiky moss_patch
;                prop, NOT baked into the walking tiles (spec §5). The ONLY green
;                source (it IS the grass layer). 768x128 = SIX 4x4 variant-blocks.
;
; DEAD: floor_slab.png (ashlar, third rejection) + floor_sandstone.png (rejected
; twice) are retired — no source references them. Kept on disk as deprecation refs.
;
; Tile size 32px matches LevelChunkDef.tile_size_px=32. Each ground tile-class is
; painted into its OWN TileMapLayer (FloorTiles=dirt base; CobblePatches; GrassPatches;
; PathLane) with exactly ONE class rendering per cell (the cell is erased in the other
; layers) — the AC9 paint-not-stack rule, z=0, no z-fight (html5-export.md §Z-index).
; Palette-locked to the doctrines inside the PNGs; the .tres declares geometry only.

